President Obama has hosted the first-ever White House Demo Day focused on inclusive entrepreneurship, welcoming startup founders from diverse backgrounds to showcase their innovations. The President announced new commitments from both the public and private sectors to provide more Americans with the opportunity to pursue their entrepreneurial ideas. These commitments include investing in entrepreneurship training programmes, creating initiatives to increase diversity in the tech workforce, and providing funding and support for underrepresented groups in entrepreneurship. The aim is to ensure that all Americans, including women and people of color, have the opportunity to contribute their entrepreneurial talents and to create a vibrant startup ecosystem in every corner of the country.